<text>The morning is gorgeous and we're up early enough to see the sunrise over the eastern peaks.  My sleeping pad is still leaking so it was a bit of a restless night as I'd have to find comfortable positions without much air in the pad and then eventually wake up enough to blow it up again.  I need to find a river with enough water in it to submerge parts of the pad so I can find where the leak is (probably in the Tuolumne River this afternoon).  It got quite cold last night (perhaps high 30s), but my sleeping bag was more than warm enough.</text>

