<text>On the descent into Tuolumne, we come upon this spring that is literally bubbling out of the ground right next to the trail and then flowing downhill.  It seems like a perfect place for a break and to grab some water as it's hard to imagine the water can get any more pure than this.  It's literally bubbling out of the side of a hill.  There must be some sort of aquifer from above that meets the surface here on the side of this hill.  Many are drinking directly from the spring, but we're still using our Steripens with their UV purifier to purify the water before drinking.

We head down the remaining portion of the descent towards Tuolumne Meadows and when it seems like we should be really close to our destination, it turns out Tuolumne Meadows is pretty long and we actually have another two miles to go to get to the Post Office and Tuolumne Grill which is our first destination (I've heard some people hop a shuttle bus for this two miles, but we walk).</text>

